{"lemma":"ظِلُّ","slug":"ظِلُّ","root":"ظ.ل.ل","root_slug":"ظ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ظِلّ","root":"ظلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":23},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27587","n27591"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shadow, shade"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reflection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shady garden"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paradise"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protection, help, assistance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dark cloud"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darkness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"night"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"phantom, specter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cover, lid, scabbard"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shape, figure, person"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Sultan (as shadow of God on Earth)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"greatness, sublimity, distinction, eminence, rareness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, night"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"colors of the day, shades of color, bloom of youth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heat of summer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fringe, hairy side of a cloth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trace"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tangent (symbol: ظا, ظل)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remain, to persist, to maintain","tags":["copulative"],"examples":[{"text":"ظَلَّ صَامِتًا","english":"He remained silent."},{"text":"ظَلَّ عَلَى مَوْقِفِهِ","english":"He maintained his point of view. [= stayed in the place he was standing]"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep doing, to do constantly, to persist in, to remain","examples":[{"text":"يَظَلُّ يَتْبَعُهَا","english":"He keeps following her."},{"text":"ظَلُّوا جَالِسِينَ","english":"They remained sitting."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ظَلَّ (ẓalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṯ̣ill- (“shadow”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒄑𒈪 (ṣillum), Ugaritic 𐎑𐎍 (ẓl) and Biblical Hebrew צל (ṣel)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27587","headword_ar":"ظَلَّ","root":"Zl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZil~u","text_ar":"يَظِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlapN","text_ar":"ظِلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, O, Msb, K,) [and accord. to SM"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalalotu","text_ar":"ظَلَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, for he says that] the verb is of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaEa","text_ar":"مَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as of the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEiba","text_ar":"تَعِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalotu","text_ar":"ظَلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, * M, O, K,) likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotu","text_ar":"لَسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, *) formed by rejecting the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zilotu","text_ar":"ظِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is [also] originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, T, M, O, K,) formed by transferring to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the vowel of the rejected"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, T, M, O,) anomalously, (Sb, M,) the latter of the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz; (T;) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZal~u","text_ar":"يَظَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * M, O, * Msb, K;) imperative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZolalo","text_ar":"اِظْلَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalo","text_ar":"ظَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T) [and it is implied in the M voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qar~a","text_ar":"قَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"that one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZolilo","text_ar":"اِظْلِلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zilo","text_ar":"ظِلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which indicates that the aor. is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaZil~u","text_ar":"يَظِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this requires confirmation, which I have not anywhere found]; inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuluwlN","text_ar":"ظُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~N","text_ar":"ظَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (thus also in a copy of the M; [but this I think doubtful;]) accord. to Lth, (T,) or Kh, (Msb,) [i. e. accord. to the author of the 'Eyn,] is said only of a thing that is done in the day, or daytimes; (T, S, M, O, Msb;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta","text_ar":"بَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiytu","text_ar":"يَبِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said only of a thing that is done in the night: (T:) it is an incomplete [i. e. a non-attributive] verb, relating to a time in which is a shade from the sun, from morning to evening, or from sunrise to sunset: (Esh-Shiháb, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN nahaArahu SaAy^imFA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ نَهَارَهُ صَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was during his day fasting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his day fasting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Lth, T:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a nahaArahu yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ نَهَارَهُ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during, his day doing such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his day doing such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalilotu A^aEomalu","text_ar":"ظَلِلْتُ اَعْمَلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was in the day"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daytime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed the day, doing such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did such a thing in the day"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daytime."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb. *) In the saying of 'Antarah,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"walaqado A^abiytu EalaY AlT~awaY waA^aZal~uhu\n                      \n                     \n                        Hat~aY A^anaAla bihi kariyma AlmaA^okali"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily I pass the night in hunger, and I pass the day in it, that I may attain thereby plentiful eating"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZal~uhu","text_ar":"اَظَلُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZal~u","text_ar":"اَظَلُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) And accord. to some, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolahu","text_ar":"لَيْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry; (M, K, TA;) so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a layolahu yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ لَيْلَهُ يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during, his night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he passed his night, doing such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but it is said that in this case the verb has the meaning next following. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, became;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra","text_ar":"صَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib, TA:) being in this sense likewise an incomplete [i. e. a non-attributive] verb, divested of that meaning of time which it radically denotes; as in the phrase in the Kur [xvi. 60 and xliii. 16],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a wajohuhu musowad~FA","text_ar":"ظَلَّ وَجْهُهُ مُسْوَدًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face becomes black"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says Ibn-Málik: (TA:) or this may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his face continues all the day black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 60:) and one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a","text_ar":"ظَلَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"يَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He continued doing such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this too is mentioned by Ibn-Málik, and is of the dial. of the people of Syria. (TA.) ―         -b3-  It is also a complete [i. e. an attributive] verb as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, continued;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is said in the Expos. of the “ Shifè, ” and by Ibn-Málik; and, as Ibn-Málik likewise says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","Msb","K","S","O","TA","Sb","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n27591","headword_ar":"ظِلٌّ","root":"Zl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shade;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of the sun without the rays:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when there is no light, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulomapN","text_ar":"ظُلْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiH~N","text_ar":"ضِحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'N","text_ar":"فَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so some say: (M:) or so the [common] people say: (IKt, Msb:) or the former is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shade"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter is in the evening: (M, K:) or, accord. to IKt, the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning and in the evening;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the latter is only after the declining of the sun from the meridian: ISk says that the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the rising of the sun to its declining;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, from the declining to the setting: Th says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tree &c. is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the evening: (Msb:) Ru-beh says, (M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which the sun has been and which it has quitted"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'N","text_ar":"فَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb;) but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which the sun has not been"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[only]; and hence it is said that the sun annuls, or supersedes, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"annuls, or supersedes, the sun: (Msb:) AHeyth says, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything upon which the sun has not come;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied only after the declining of the sun; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being eastwards and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being westwards; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the beginning of the day to the declining of the sun;"},{"kind":"text","text":"after which it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"until the night: (T, TA:) one says the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Paradise, but not its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", because the sun will never replace its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but En-Nábighah El-Jaadee has assigned to Paradise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAl","text_ar":"ظِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) in a verse of Aboo-Sakhr ElHudhalee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made fem. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maniy~ap","text_ar":"مَنِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ham p. 161:) the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlN","text_ar":"ظِلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuluwlN","text_ar":"ظُلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZolaAlN","text_ar":"اَظْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, O, K.) The saying of a rájiz,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kaA^an~amaA wajohuka Zil~N mino Hajaro"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As though thy face were a shade of a stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said to mean hardness of face, and shamelessness: or the being black in the face: (T, TA:) for the Arabs say that there is nothing more dense in shade than a stone. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado DaHaA Zil~uhu","text_ar":"قَدْ ضَحَا ظِلُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shadow, has become sun"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of the dead. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a binaA kaA^an~ahu Zil~u *iy^obK","text_ar":"مَرَّ بِنَا كَاَنَّهُ ظِلُّ ذِيْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed by us as though he were the shadow of a wolf"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means swiftly, as does a wolf. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinotaEalato","text_ar":"اِنْتَعَلَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlahaA","text_ar":"ظِلَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They made their shadows to be as though they were sandals to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of camels or other beasts when it is midday in summer and they have no shadow [but such as is beneath them]: a rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado waradato tamo$iY EalaY ZilaAlihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        wa*aAbati Al$~amosu EalaY qilaAlihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came to the water walking upon their shadows, and the sun was intensely hot upon the tops of their heads and humps"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yatobaEu Zil~a nafosihi","text_ar":"هُوَ يَتْبَعُ ظِلَّ نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He follows the shadow of himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. a thing that he will not overtake; for], as a poet says, the shadow that goes with thee thou wilt not overtake by following: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yubaAriY Zil~a nafosihi","text_ar":"هُوَ يُبَارِى ظِلَّ نَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strives to outstrip the shadow of himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning that he walks with a proud and self-conceited gait: so in the A. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainotaqalotu Eano Zil~iY","text_ar":"اِنْتَقَلْتُ عَنْ ظِلِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I left my state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka AlZ~aboYu Zil~ahu","text_ar":"تَرَكَ الظَّبْىُ ظِلَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the T and S and O: (TA:) but [said to be] correctly,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atorukuhu taroka AlZ~aboYi Zil~ahu","text_ar":"اَتْرُكُهُ تَرْكَ الظَّبْىِ ظِلَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^atorukan~ahu","text_ar":"لَاَتْرُكَنَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will forsake him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly forsake him, as the gazelle forsakes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of its shade:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) [each, however, is app. right; and the former is the more agreeable with the following explanations:] a prov., (M,) applied to the man who is wont to take fright and flee; for the gazelle, when it takes fright and flees from a thing, never returns to it: (S, O, K:) by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here meant the covert in which it shades and shelters itself in the vehemence of the heat; then the hunter comes to it and rouses it, and it will not return thither; and one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraka AlZ~aboYu Zil~ahu","text_ar":"تَرَكَ الظَّبْىُ ظِلَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning the place of its shade: it is applied to him who takes fright and flees from a thing, and forsakes it so as not to return to it; and to the case of a man's forsaking his companion. (Meyd.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaqiylu AlZ~il~i","text_ar":"ثَقِيلُ الظِّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a man, see expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vql","text_ar":"ثقل"},{"kind":"text","text":": see also Har p. 250, where it is indicated that it may be rendered One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose shadow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"even,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is oppressive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore much more so is his person.] In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA A@lZ~il~u walaA A@loHaruwru","text_ar":"وَلَا ا@لظِّلُّ وَلَا ا@لْحَرُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K) in the Kur [xxxv. 20], Th says, accord. to some, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~u","text_ar":"الظِّلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaruwru","text_ar":"الحَرُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the fire [of Hell]: but he adds, I say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~u","text_ar":"الظِّلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shade"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaruwru","text_ar":"الحَرُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~","text_ar":"حَرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself [i. e. heat]: (M: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaruwrN","text_ar":"حَرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and Er-Rághib says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes assigned to anything; whether it be approved, as in the phrase above mentioned; or disapproved, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZil~K mino yaHomuwmK","text_ar":"وَظِلٍّ مِنْ يَحْمُومٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [lvi. 42, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And shade of smoke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black smoke"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ilaAlu","text_ar":"الظِّلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlu Aljan~api","text_ar":"ظِلَالُ الجَنَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The shades of Paradise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Fr, T, O, K, TA:) in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlZ~ilaAlu","text_ar":"وَالظِّلَالُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljan~apu","text_ar":"الجَنَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mistake: (TA:) [but this requires consideration; for] El-'Abbás Ibn- 'Abd-El-Muttalib says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"mino qabolihaA Tibota fiY AlZ~ilaAli wafiY\n                      \n                     \n                        musotawodaEK Hayovu yuxoSafu Alwaraqu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Before it thou wast good in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the shades of, Paradise, and in a depositary in the part where leaves are sewed together to conceal the pudenda"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, O, TA;) i. e. before thy descent to the earth (to which the pronoun in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qblhA","text_ar":"قبلها"},{"kind":"text","text":"relates), thou wast good in the loins of Adam when he was in Paradise. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljan~apu taHota ZilaAli Als~uyuwfi","text_ar":"الجَنَّةُ تَحْتَ ظِلَالِ السُّيُوفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise is beneath the shades of the swords"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a trad., meaning that fighting against unbelievers is a way of attaining to Paradise. (Marg. note in a copy of the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEibu Zil~ihi","text_ar":"مُلَاعِبُ ظِلِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEb","text_ar":"لعب"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEibaA Zil~ihimaA","text_ar":"مُلَاعِبَا ظِلِّهِمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEibaAtu","text_ar":"مُلَاعِبَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~ihin~a","text_ar":"ظِلِّهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but when you make them indeterminate, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaAEibaAtu A^aZolaAlihin~a","text_ar":"مُلَاعِبَاتُ اَظْلَالِهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, O, K. [But in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEb","text_ar":"لعب"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said that one dualizes and pluralizes both nouns, because the appellation becomes determinate.]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~u All~ayoli","text_ar":"ظِلُّ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The blackness of the night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, O, Msb;) metaphorically thus termed; (S;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAnaA fiY Zil~i All~ayoli","text_ar":"اَتَانَا فِى ظِلِّ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came to us in the blackness of the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junoHu All~ayoli","text_ar":"جُنْحُ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confusedness, of the night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junoHN","text_ar":"جُنْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, TA;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~il~u","text_ar":"الظِّلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) so the astronomers say: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and so is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all the period from the shining of the dawn to the rising of the sun."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~u Aln~ahaAri","text_ar":"ظِلُّ النَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is The colour of the day when the sun predominates over it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the light of the sun predominates over that of the early dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~u","text_ar":"ظِلُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such, of the clouds, as conceal the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the blackness of the clouds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAlu AlbaHori","text_ar":"ظِلَالُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The waves of the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA;) because they are raised so as to shade the ship and those that are in it. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaAl","text_ar":"خَيَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is seen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an apparition, a phantom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that one sees like a shadow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. what we term"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the jinn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genii,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayaAl","text_ar":"خَيَال"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the jinn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b7-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that shades one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  And it is the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZal~aniY Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"اَظَلَّنِى الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ the thing covered me; ” (M, K;) [i. e. it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A covering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in which sense Th explains it in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY Zil~K *iY valaAvi $uEabK","text_ar":"اـِلَى ظِلٍّ ذِى ثَلَاثِ شُعَبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur lxxvii. 30,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unto a covering having three parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divisions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; saying, the meaning is that the fire will have covered them; not that its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"will be like that of the present world. (M. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uEobapN","text_ar":"شُعْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~u Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"ظِلُّ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That which serves for the veiling, covering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protecting, of the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kin~uhu","text_ar":"كِنُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) [Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yaEiy$u fiY Zil~i fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَعِيشُ فِى ظِلِّ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one lives"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the shelter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protection, of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, O, Msb, * K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uloTaAnu Zil~u A@ll~`hi fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"السُّلْطَانُ ظِلُّ ا@للّٰهِ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) a saying of the Prophet, (O,) [meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sovereign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruling, power is God's means of defence in the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because he wards off"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1916},{"kind":"text","text":"harm from the people like as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so called] wards off the harm of the heat of the sun: (TA:) or the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God's means of protection:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAS~ap","text_ar":"خَاصَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special servant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b9-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Might;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power of resistance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) whence [as some say] its usage in the Kur xiii. 35, and the usage of [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZilaAl","text_ar":"ظِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"in xxxvi. 56 and in lxxvii. 41: [but the primary signification is more appropriate in these instances:] and so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalaniY fiY Zil~ihi","text_ar":"جَعَلَنِى فِى ظِلِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He placed me within the scope of his might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power of resistance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says Er-Rághib. (TA.) ―         -b10-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state"},{"kind":"text","text":"of life"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample in its means"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances, unstraitened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful, and easy, pleasant, soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginning"},{"kind":"text","text":"of winter. (T, O. [Accord. to the copies of the K, of youthfulness: but I think that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~abaAb","text_ar":"الشَّبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance, in the K, is evidently a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~itaA='","text_ar":"الشِّتَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O) of summer. (T, O, K.) ―         -b12-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoS","text_ar":"شَخْص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being, and as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corporeal form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figure"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance which one sees from a distance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"material substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of anything; (M, K, TA; [in the second and third of which is added, “ or its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kin~","text_ar":"كِنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ” a signification which I have mentioned above on the authority of the M;]) because of its [apparent] blackness [or darkness, resembling that of a shade or shadow]: (M, TA:) whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yufaAriqu Zil~iY Zil~aka","text_ar":"لَا يُفَارِقُ ظِلِّى ظِلَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My person will not quit thy person"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yufaAriqu","text_ar":"لَا يُفَارِقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAdiY sawaAdaka","text_ar":"سَوَادِى سَوَادَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the following exs. have been cited as instances of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$axoS","text_ar":"شَخْص"},{"kind":"text","text":": the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lam~aA nazalonaA rafaEonaA Zil~a A^axobiyapK"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When we alighted, we raised the material fabric of tents"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for it is said that they do not set up the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'","text_ar":"فَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", but they only set up the tents; and the saying of another,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tatab~aEa A^afoyaA='a AlZ~ilaAli Ea$iy~apF"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He followed the shadows of the material objects in the evening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but Er-Rághib says that the former means, we raised the tents, and so raised the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~","text_ar":"ظِلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; and in the other ex.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZlAl","text_ar":"الظلال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a general term, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaYo'","text_ar":"الفَىْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfyA='","text_ar":"افيا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a special term, so that it is an instance of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iDaAfap","text_ar":"اـِضَافَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing to its kind [i. e. of prefixing a noun to one significant of its kind]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalaAlapN","text_ar":"ظَلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b13-  And accord. to Ibn- 'Abbád, (O,) it signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villous substance, upon the surface of a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziy^obirN","text_ar":"زِيْبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","M","K","IKt","Msb","T","TA","Fr"]}]}}